  "text": "To give a concrete illustration of input determined automata, we show how the event clock automata of [CITATION_1] can be realized in the above framework. Take Op to be the set of operators {⊳ a , ⊲ a | a ∈ Σ}, where the operators ⊳ a and ⊲ a essentially record the time since the last a action, and the time to the next a action. The operator ⊳ a (and similarly ⊲ a ) can be defined here by setting ⊳ a (σ, i) to be {I ∈ I Q | ∃j < i : σ(j) = a, τ (i) − τ (j) ∈ I, and ∀k : j < k < i, σ(k) = a}.",
